prompt:
Add a public function called PrintNumbers to Effects.calr that prints numbers from 1 to 5 using a for loop. The function takes no parameters and returns void. It needs the console write effect (cw).

Use this exact Calor for-loop syntax:
§F{f001:PrintNumbers:pub}
  §O{void}
  §E{cw}
  §L{l001:i:1:5:1}
    §C{Console.WriteLine}
      §A i
    §/C
  §/L{l001}
§/F{f001}

The §L{id:var:from:to:step} syntax creates a for loop where:
- id is a unique loop identifier (l001)
- var is the loop variable name (i)
- from is the start value (1)
- to is the end value (5)
- step is the increment (1)
